        <h2>Content Authoring and Accessibility</h2>

        <p>Content creation involves defining a content strategy, the writing or creation of the content or media for a product. The person who authors the content is responsible for making sure that content is accessible to people with disabilities. This role includes content strategy and content authoring, including audio/video production.</p>

        <h3>Key Responsibilities</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Creating accessible text content with proper structure and language</li>
            <li>Writing clear and understandable content for diverse audiences</li>
            <li>Ensuring proper heading structure and semantic markup</li>
            <li>Creating accessible alternative text for images and media</li>
            <li>Developing content strategies that prioritize accessibility</li>
            <li>Writing scripts for accessible audio and video content</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Content Authoring Tasks</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Content authoring with accessibility principles</li>
            <li>Media and documentation creation</li>
            <li>Content strategies definition</li>
            <li>Writing guidelines development</li>
            <li>Transcript and caption creation</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Content Publishing Tasks</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Advanced tagging in PDF documents</li>
            <li>Adjusting timing of captions</li>
            <li>Creating and editing transcripts</li>
            <li>Conversion to accessible ePUB documentation</li>
            <li>Applying semantic tags for proper heading structure</li>
        </ul>

